/img/work/ryan-duggan.jpg";s:14:"largethumbnail";s:56:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/ryan-duggan-screen-large.jpg";s:8:"features";s:0:"";s:5:"about";s:627:"<p>
	 Ryan Duggan is an awesome artist, and a great dude, known well in Chicago for his concert posters, hand-lettering, and his skateboard company <em>Hated</em>. Ryan is always working like a mad man, and his portfolio of commissions and artwork is constantly growing. His last website was made up of static HTML files that he would have to hack around every time he wanted to change or add something new. He hired me to help create a new site that was easy to update and maintain, looked great, and was accessible on phones and other small-screen devices for the various expos and festivals that he sells his prints at.
</p>";s:4:"role";s:613:"<p>
	 I worked with Ryan to come up with a simple design that focused on showcasing his portfolio of work, while maintaining his signature style and personality. I built out a custom Wordpress theme that allowed Ryan the ability to add new work easily, and have the content and information fit in seamlessly with the design. I created a responsive layout that presents the work perfectly no matter what screen size it's view on. In order to help improve site performance with the large amount of images displayed on the site, I implemented a way to automatically losslessly compress any new images Ryan adds.
</p>";s:7:"content";s:4:"true";s:11:"content_raw";s:4:"true";s:5:"_file";s:79:"/Users/Starchild/Sites/mattsoria/_content/1-work/2014-01-01-2032-ryan-duggan.md";s:11:"_local_path";s:38:"/1-work/2014-01-01-2032-ryan-duggan.md";s:10:"_order_key";i:1388619120;s:13:"datetimestamp";N;s:9:"datestamp";i:1388619120;s:4:"date";s:13:"Jan 1st, 2014";s:4:"time";s:10:"8:32.00 pm";s:7:"numeric";N;s:13:"last_modified";i:1390306423;s:10:"_is_hidden";b:0;s:9:"_is_draft";b:0;s:7:"_folder";s:4:"work";s:4:"slug";s:11:"ryan-duggan";s:9:"_basename";s:30:"2014-01-01-2032-ryan-duggan.md";s:9:"_filename";s:27:"2014-01-01-2032-ryan-duggan";s:9:"_is_entry";i:1;s:8:"_is_page";i:0;s:3:"url";s:17:"/work/ryan-duggan";s:9:"permalink";s:33:"http://mattsoria/work/ryan-duggan";}s:32:"/1-work/2014-01-02-1841-atlas.md";a:39:{s:5:"image";s:39:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/atlasmd.jpg";s:5:"title";s:8:"Atlas.md";s:10:"categories";a:1:{i:0;s:21:"front-end development";}s:11:"description";s:205:"I was tasked with the front-end  development for the sales site of Atlas.md, a  new EMR web app. I built out the site  responsively, and addressed the many  challenges of great-looking, accessible  images.";s:9:"_template";s:7:"project";s:10:"largeimage";s:45:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/atlasmd-large.jpg";s:10:"smallimage";s:45:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/atlasmd-small.jpg";s:12:"smallimage2x";s:48:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/atlasmd-small-2x.jpg";s:8:"medimage";s:46:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/atlasmd-medium.jpg";s:10:"medimage2x";s:49:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/atlasmd-medium-2x.jpg";s:12:"largeimage2x";s:48:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/atlasmd-large-2x.jpg";s:4:"year";s:4:"2013";s:7:"siteurl";s:19:"http://www.atlas.md";s:9:"thumbnail";s:39:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/atlasmd.jpg";s:14:"largethumbnail";s:45:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/atlasmd-large.jpg";s:5:"about";s:745:"<p>
	    Atlas.md is a new <strong>EMR</strong> web application built by the awesome team at Entermotion that was designed to make managing patient records, appointments, prescriptions and communication easy for health care practices and doctors. The goal of the app is to simplify the hassle of all the paperwork involved in healthcare, and let doctors focus on what really matters: caring for their patients. The sales site for Atlas.md is responsible for conveying the many ways in which the app will benefit medical practices that adopt its usage, and for onboarding new users. The site highlights various features of the application to help potential users understand the breadth of its capabilities, not to mention how great it looks!
</p>";s:4:"role";s:772:"<p>
	    I was tasked with building out the front-end code for the sales site, which presented many interesting challenges to overcome. The design team created a beautiful layout that highlights various features of the app, and illustrates its capabilities to be used on any device or screen size. This yielded very specific layouts in each section that required me to do some creative coding and problem solving in order to make it fully responsive - which it is. The large images and screenshots used to show off the app's great design were quite large and heavy, especially when serving higher resolution versions for retina displays, so I needed to employ some responsive image techniques to ensure that the site loads quickly no matter what you're viewing it on.
</p>";s:8:"features";s:136:"<ul>
	<li>HTML + CSS</li>
	<li>jQuery</li>
	<li>responsive design</li>
	<li>retina display images</li>
	<li>responsive images</li>
</ul>";s:7:"content";s:4:"true";s:11:"content_raw";s:4:"true";s:5:"_file";s:73:"/Users/Starchild/Sites/mattsoria/_content/1-work/2014-01-02-1841-atlas.md";s:11:"_local_path";s:32:"/1-work/2014-01-02-1841-atlas.md";s:10:"_order_key";i:1388698860;s:13:"datetimestamp";N;s:9:"datestamp";i:1388698860;s:4:"date";s:13:"Jan 2nd, 2014";s:4:"time";s:10:"6:41.00 pm";s:7:"numeric";N;s:13:"last_modified";i:1390303211;s:10:"_is_hidden";b:0;s:9:"_is_draft";b:0;s:7:"_folder";s:4:"work";s:4:"slug";s:5:"atlas";s:9:"_basename";s:24:"2014-01-02-1841-atlas.md";s:9:"_filename";s:21:"2014-01-02-1841-atlas";s:9:"_is_entry";i:1;s:8:"_is_page";i:0;s:3:"url";s:11:"/work/atlas";s:9:"permalink";s:27:"http://mattsoria/work/atlas";}s:31:"/1-work/2014-01-12-1953-agsc.md";a:39:{s:5:"image";s:36:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/agsc.jpg";s:5:"title";s:4:"AGSC";s:9:"_template";s:7:"project";s:10:"categories";a:2:{i:0;s:4:"logo";i:1;s:6:"design";}s:11:"description";s:112:"A non-profit organization in Kentucky approached me to do a logo for them to help with identity and fundraising.";s:10:"largeimage";s:50:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/agsc-logo-textured.jpg";s:10:"smallimage";s:50:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/agsc-logo-textured.jpg";s:12:"smallimage2x";s:53:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/agsc-logo-textured-2x.jpg";s:8:"medimage";s:50:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/agsc-logo-textured.jpg";s:10:"medimage2x";s:53:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/agsc-logo-textured-2x.jpg";s:12:"largeimage2x";s:53:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/agsc-logo-textured-2x.jpg";s:4:"year";s:4:"2013";s:7:"siteurl";s:0:"";s:9:"thumbnail";s:36:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/agsc.jpg";s:14:"largethumbnail";s:42:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/work/agsc-large.jpg";s:8:"features";s:0:"";s:5:"about";s:657:"<p>
	  The <a href="http://www.appalachianglobalservicecorps.org/">Appalachian Global Service Corps</a> is a non-profit organization based in the Appalachian Mountains of Southeastern Kentucky, dedicated to developing global citizenship, leadership skills, and  language abilities of Appalachian youth through life-altering service  learning. Preceding a funding campaign to help 15 students travel to Peru for two weeks of experiential service and a cultural immersion experience, they approached me to design a logo that would help unify their identity and express their mission.
</p>
<p>
	<a href="http://www.appalachianglobalservicecorps.org/"></a>
</p>";s:4:"role";s:743:"<p>
	  I worked together with the founders of the organization to identify various visuals and themes that would help portray both the organization's roots, as well as its mission. I presented them with a series of sketches and ideas, and we narrowed down the visuals to what was really important to express through the logo. Inspired by various scout badges from the 50's and 60's, I created a circular composition that includes the rolling peaks of the Appalachian Mountains, a shining sun, and a cross made up of a shovel and pencil, to symbolize the physical and academic efforts of the organization and its volunteers. I reworked some of the main elements of the logo into various compositions to be used in a multitude of scenarios.
</p>";s:7:"content";s:4:"true";s:11:"content_raw";s:4:"true";s:5:"_file";s:72:"/Users/Starchild/Sites/mattsoria/_content/1-work/2014-01-12-1953-agsc.md";s:11:"_local_path";s:31:"/1-work/2014-01-12-1953-agsc.md";s:10:"_order_key";i:1389567180;s:13:"datetimestamp";N;s:9:"datestamp";i:1389567180;s:4:"date";s:14:"Jan 12th, 2014";s:4:"time";s:10:"7:53.00 pm";s:7:"numeric";N;s:13:"last_modified";i:1390307639;s:10:"_is_hidden";b:0;s:9:"_is_draft";b:0;s:7:"_folder";s:4:"work";s:4:"slug";s:4:"agsc";s:9:"_basename";s:23:"2014-01-12-1953-agsc.md";s:9:"_filename";s:20:"2014-01-12-1953-agsc";s:9:"_is_entry";i:1;s:8:"_is_page";i:0;s:3:"url";s:10:"/work/agsc";s:9:"permalink";s:26:"http://mattsoria/work/agsc";}s:15:"/1-work/page.md";a:21:{s:5:"title";s:4:"Work";s:9:"_template";s:4:"work";s:5:"_file";s:56:"/Users/Starchild/Sites/mattsoria/_content/1-work/page.md";s:11:"_local_path";s:15:"/1-work/page.md";s:10:"_order_key";s:7:"page.md";s:13:"datetimestamp";N;s:9:"datestamp";N;s:4:"date";N;s:4:"time";N;s:7:"numeric";N;s:13:"last_modified";i:1390294041;s:10:"_is_hidden";b:0;s:9:"_is_draft";b:0;s:7:"_folder";s:4:"work";s:4:"slug";s:4:"page";s:9:"_basename";s:7:"page.md";s:9:"_filename";s:4:"page";s:9:"_is_entry";i:0;s:8:"_is_page";i:1;s:3:"url";s:5:"/work";s:9:"permalink";s:21:"http://mattsoria/work";}s:45:"/2-play/2013-12-31-1111-balance-is-fragile.md";a:25:{s:5:"image";s:60:"/_themes/mattsoria/img/play/9-19-2012-balance-is-fragile.jpg";s:5:"title";s:18:"Balance is fragile";s:10:"categories";a:1:{i:0;s:12:"illustration";}s:9:"_template";s:17:"play-illustration";s:7:"content";s:4:"true";s:11:"content_raw";s:4:"true";s:5:"_file";s:86:"/Users/Starchild/Sites/mattsoria/_content/2-play/2013-12-31-1111-balance-is-fragile.md";s:11:"_local_path";s:45:"/2-play/2013-12-31-1111-balance-is-fragile.md";s:10:"_order_key";i:1388499060;s:13:"datetimestamp";N;s:9:"datestamp";i:1388499060;s:4:"date";s:14:"Dec 31st, 2013";s:4:"time";s:11:"11:11.00 am";s:7:"numeric";N;s:13:"last_modified";i:1390294042;s: